    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

I will have funds requisitioned and sent along with this missive - you will no doubt need some rings to conduct business, provision help, and coerce the obstinate.

You are now a rather important target to some. Speak with Lohara, one of the master [url=glossary:forge-bound]Forge-Bound[/url]. As of this writing she is in [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url], overseeing [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' armory. Tell her I am calling in her settlement on your behalf and that she is to armor you for war. If she claims ignorance, remind her that the original punishment of dismemberment can still be enforced...

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

The [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] is more a river than an organization. Lives shuffle in and out with no guarantee that any one member will remain in one place - or even alive - long enough to make a difference. However, there are a few gang captains that have run afoul of my law of late that showed a willingness for penance. I sent them back to camp with instructions to speak well of the Fatebinder of the Spire. I cannot guarantee this will accomplish much. If you wish to earn the respect of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url], you must take it - serve their needs or impress them with your strength. Asking, requesting, or debating is often a losing proposition with those fully enamored with the Chorus mindset.

Do not imagine any favor will cause their reception of you to become favorable if you have otherwise garnered their ire, Fatebinder. I have done what I am able. The rest is up to you.

I would still be wary

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Peça algum goodwill com o [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url].</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Senhor [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url],

Eu preciso falar com os membros do [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] para aprender o seu lado dos acontecimentos até agora.

A legião parece ser insular e bem unida. Embora isso pareça útil e necessário para a guerra, resulta em silêncio e mentiras de omissões quando faço perguntas.

Se você é capaz, meu senhor [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url], por favor, coloque em uma palavra boa para mim, um relacionamento positivo com a legião ajudaria muito a minha investigação.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

I have sent word directly to [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url], informing him that you will be my chosen agent on recent judicial matters.

I have vouched for you character. However, do not think that mere words are enough to cause them to stay their hand if your actions have incited war in their hearts. My words carry weight, but your deeds will stay in their minds for much longer. 

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

If you wish to gain the trust of the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url], you will need to earn it - I cannot assist.

Try to appeal to the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url]'s sense of honor, duty, and tradition. Be mindful of their arrogance - they are easily offended by perceived slights to their greatness.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

I have no doubts about your loyalty. Your results, however, remain in question.

It is imperative that we do all we can to cease hostilities between the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] - and waiting for one side to annihilate the other, while technically a solution, is also dereliction of duty.

Endeavor to understand and judge fairly.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

Your tone may be puerile but you include a salient point - it falls upon me to keep the peace between Archons and their armies. So yes, as my loyal subject, I do indeed require your help to resolve this situation.

If [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] does find me negligent in matters, rest assured that all of my Fatebinders will be rounded up and buried with me.

Next time you adopt this tone, there had best be answers and results along with it.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

It is unclear from your tone if you are attempting to anger me or test my reaction. In either case, you are only half-successful.

I sense you may be a growing concern - I will ensure that [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] keeps a closer eye on you.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
